reviewText: The physical aspect of this comedy is tremendous; Gina Yashere has the moves ... I choked laughing at the Trinidadian Carnivale bit; it was perfect timing. With lines like "toes look like dry twigs" and a few other phrases of particular note, this lady moves on up in the ranks of my favorite comediennes.
Title: Gina Yahere: Skinny B*tch

reviewText: Really didn't know much about her and took a flyer. She was funny and I would look for another performance of her work.

reviewText: I love comedy but let's be real there is a survire lack of great female comics. I was really impressed by Gina. Some of her jokes were obvious but she knows what she is doing and she knows how to get a laugh. I would watch her again and if she comes to my town I will go see her.
Title: Gina Yahere: Skinny B*tch

reviewText: Side splitting funny, universal comedy, she picks on ALL of us! After laughing so hard with Gina, I shared her video with my family. My daughters and I can't wait to see her (hopefully) in So. Calif.
Title: Gina Yahere: Skinny B*tch

reviewText: What an amazing stand up Comedy!!!!  I saw her on 1st Amendment and then I began to browse and ran into this stand up and I must say what an amazing woman and funny!!! Love it!!!
Title: Gina Yahere: Skinny B*tch

reviewText: I had never heard of Gina, but this recording of her act was free on Prime. I watched it and LMAO. This is a very funny comedienne, and her humor is not the insulting kind popular among many. One caution... If you are hard of hearing, you should listen with headphones of good quality, because she has an English accent, and accents are always tough for the hearing impaired.
Title: Gina Yahere: Skinny B*tch
